title: Leader in Nuclear Energy Production
description: In 2023, 64.17% of France's electricity was produced from nuclear sources, the highest percentage in the world.

title: Top Female Primary School Enrollment
description: In 2016, France achieved a 99.65% adjusted net enrollment rate for primary school-aged girls, one of the highest globally.

title: Lowest Rate of Girls Out of School
description: In 2016, only 0.03% of primary school-aged girls in France were out of school, the lowest rate worldwide.

title: Fewest Internally Displaced People
description: As of 2022, France had only 10 internally displaced people, one of the lowest numbers globally.
